:css
  body {
      padding: 0%;
      /*display: none;*/

  }
  .span12.text-center{
      margin: 0;
  }
  fieldset.btn.profile{
    width: 82.9%;
  }
  table tr td div{
     word-wrap: break-word;
     width: 100px;
  }

  @media(min-width:100px)and(max-width: 790px){

      fieldset.btn{
          /*display: none;*/
          border: none;
          padding: 0%;
          text-align: center;


          font-size: 100%;

      }
      .span6.text-center.small-screen{
        display: block;
        width: auto;

      }
      .span6.text-center.large-screen{
        display: none;


      }
      .span6.text-center{
        margin: 0px;
      }
       table tr td,table tr th{
         font-size: 80%;
       }
      table tr td div{
         width: 50px;
      }
      fieldset.btn.profile{
        width: 100%;
      }
      able tr td a.btn.btn-mini{
        display: none;
        width: 50px;
        font-size: 80%;
        height: 20px;
      }
  }

.span12.text-center
  %fieldset.btn.profile

    The following
    = @services.count == 1 ? 'account is' : 'accounts are'
    connected with your local account:
    %table.table.table-striped
      %tr
        %th
        %th
          Name
        %th
          Email
        %th
          Uid
        %th
      - @services.each do |service|
        %tr
          %td
            = image_tag "#{service.provider}.png", size: '30x30'
          %td
            = service.uname
          %td
            = service.uemail != '' ? service.uemail : 'not set'
          %td
            = service.uid
          %td{style: 'text-align: right'}
            - @services.count == 1 ? @msg = 'Removing the last account linked might lock you out of your account if you do not know the email/password sign-in of your local account!' : @msg = ''
            = link_to 'Remove this service', service, :confirm => 'Are you sure you want to remove this authentication service? ' + @msg, :method => :delete, :class => 'btn btn-danger'
    You can connect more services to your account:
    %br
    %a{href: '/auth/facebook'}
      = image_tag 'f.png', size: '50x50', alt: 'Facebook'
    %a{href: '/auth/twitter'}
      = image_tag 't.png', size: '50x50', alt: 'Twitter'
    %a{href: '/auth/google'}
      = image_tag 'g.2.png', size: '50x50', alt: 'Twitter'
    %br
    If you signed-up for CommunityGuides via an authentication service a random password has been set for the local password.
    You can request a new password using the "Forgot your Password?" link on the sign-in page.